BENIN  – The management of Edo City Transport Service (ECTS) has vowed to sustain free rides for school children despite hikes in the prices of petroleum products. Mrs. Edugie Agbonlahor, managing director of the agency, disclosed this while fielding questions from jour­nalists in Benin City, the state capital. She declared that the fa­vourable policies of Governor Goodwin Obaseki had helped to transform and sustain the agency. Port Protest: FG Urged To Revert VIN Valuation, Curb Inflation Sanwo-Olu Dedicates Independent, Silverbird Awards To Lagosians Mrs. Edugie also hinted of plans by the local govern­ment areas to three others in the state ECTS to extend its coverage from 15. “In compliance with the government policy on a free ride for school children, many parents are no longer burdened anymore on how their children get to school because of the free services ECTS is offering.